http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date Tue 29 Dec 2015
Source: UOL Noticias [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://noticias.uol.com.br/saude/ultimas-noticias/redacao/2015/12/29/rn-investiga-morte-por-febre-amarela-em-1-caso-apos-73-anos.htm


Rio Grande do Norte investigates a yellow fever [YF] death - the 1st case in 73 years
------
The state Secretariat of Public Health of Rio Grande do Norte (SESAP) reported that this Tuesday (29 [Dec 2015]) they are investigating the death of a woman in July [2015] in Natal for which tests gave a positive result for yellow fever (YF). This case has attracted attention because the state is not classified as a YF risk area by the Ministry of Health and there have been no occurrences in the region. The victim had not traveled to YF-endemic areas [another hypothesis that always must be investigated is the possibility that this is a complication of a serious post-YF vaccination adverse effect. - Mod.RNA]

The tests [which ones? serological? virus isolation? PCR? immunohistochemistry? - Mod.RNA] that identified the disease were done by laboratories of the Instituto Evandro Chagas in Belem and in the Instituto Adolfo Lutz, in Sao Paulo. Both are national reference laboratories for testing of this type.

The victim was a nursing aid in RCSS and was 53 years old. She was hospitalized on 2 Jul [2015] and died 4 days later [due to clinical complications? - Mod.RNA]. The case is being jointly evaluated by the Natal Secretariat of Health and by the Ministry of Health. Both the state and the municipality request tests to confirm or reject the disease [diagnosis] [confirm or reject in another laboratory and not in the reference laboratories that provided positive results? confirm or reject by means of another laboratory technique? - Mod.RNA].

According to information from SESAP, the patient presented with symptoms similar to those of dengue or Zika [virus infections], but these 2 diseases were ruled out by laboratory tests. From then on, research on other viral diseases was initiated [based on the clinical picture or syndrome? - Mod.RNA], which culminated with finding the YF virus.

SESAP was intrigued with the case. "As of the present time, we still have not encountered a clear explanation for the initial results, since there is no history of patient travel to endemic areas and no other cases were detected in the [Natal] municipality," they stated.

With these questions, action to collect insects and biological materials from primates for virus investigation is being done [and active searching for other possible human cases? - Mod.RNA]. "One of the hypotheses is that the tests were positive due to the patient having been vaccinated against YF, even though decades have passed. [if the patient was in fact vaccinated sometime in the past, some protection would be expected. - Mod.RNA]. An investigation of her vaccination history is being done in health units, and the Ministry is aware of the possibility of conducting more detailed laboratory tests," it was stated [which tests? was a necropsy done? immunohistochemistry done? - Mod.RNA].

According to the Natal Secretariat of Health, routine and constant collection of _Aedes aegypti_ (the possible vector that transmits the disease [virus]) is carried out in Natal, and then tested for viruses, and there is no record of YF [virus detection].

--
